1
00:00:07,758 --> 00:00:12,137
[ INDISTINCT
CONVERSATIONS ]

2
00:00:12,137 --> 00:00:15,557
YOU'LL WIN IN EIGHT MOVES.

3
00:00:15,557 --> 00:00:18,226
YOU'RE REALLY STARTING TO GET
A FEEL FOR THE GAME.

4
00:00:18,226 --> 00:00:21,313
32 PIECES, 64 SQUARES.

5
00:00:21,313 --> 00:00:23,273
IT'S NOT AS IF
IT'S DIFFICULT.

6
00:00:23,273 --> 00:00:26,276
THE TOTAL NUMBER OF POSSIBLE
OUTCOMES<i> IS</i> LIMITED.

7
00:00:26,276 --> 00:00:29,321
10 TO THE 123rd POWER.

8
00:00:29,321 --> 00:00:30,489
THAT'S WHAT I MEAN.

9
00:00:30,489 --> 00:00:32,366
CHESS IS SO PREDICTABLE.

10
00:00:32,366 --> 00:00:35,118
I'M SURPRISED
ANYONE BOTHERS TO PLAY IT.

11
00:00:35,118 --> 00:00:38,455
THEIR AVERAGE LIFESPAN'S
ONLY ABOUT 100 YEARS,

12
00:00:38,455 --> 00:00:41,124
WITH NO TIME TO PLAY
ALL THE POSSIBLE GAMES.

13
00:00:41,124 --> 00:00:43,502
-WHAT A WASTE.
-CAREFUL.

14
00:00:43,502 --> 00:00:46,087
NO EMOTIONAL INVOLVEMENT.

15
00:00:46,087 --> 00:00:47,297
I KNOW THE RULES.

16
00:00:47,297 --> 00:00:49,550
OBSERVATION
WITHOUT INTERFERENCE.

17
00:00:51,343 --> 00:00:52,427
HMM.

18
00:00:55,597 --> 00:00:57,224
YOU'LL WIN IN FIVE MOVES.

19
00:00:57,224 --> 00:00:59,476
I'M THE SHIP'S CHAMPION.

20
00:00:59,476 --> 00:01:02,396
I WIN ALL THE TOURNAMENTS.

21
00:01:02,396 --> 00:01:04,398
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

22
00:01:04,398 --> 00:01:07,067
HOW DO YOU THINK THEY'LL REACT
TO WHAT'S ON THIS PLANET?

23
00:01:07,067 --> 00:01:11,488
WELL, THAT'S WHAT WE'RE HERE
TO FIND OUT.

24
00:01:11,488 --> 00:01:14,742
BUT IN MY EXPERIENCE, ALL
PHYSICAL SPECIES ARE ALIKE.

25
00:01:14,742 --> 00:01:17,036
I DON'T EXPECT
HUMANS WILL BE ANY DIFFERENT.

26
00:01:17,036 --> 00:01:19,580
DO YOU THINK
OUR HOSTS WILL DIE TONIGHT?

27
00:01:19,580 --> 00:01:21,498
IT'S POSSIBLE.

28
00:01:21,498 --> 00:01:23,918
FOR SOME OF THE SPECIES
THAT HAVE COME HERE,

29
00:01:23,918 --> 00:01:26,294
I'VE SEEN THE WHOLE CREW DIE.

30
00:01:26,294 --> 00:01:28,171
FOR OTHERS, ONLY A FEW.

31
00:01:28,171 --> 00:01:30,674
BUT SOMEBODY ALWAYS DIES.

32
00:01:30,674 --> 00:01:32,593
ALWAYS.

33
00:01:35,178 --> 00:01:37,222
YOUR MOVE.

34
00:01:37,222 --> 00:01:40,017
[ SIGHS ]

35
00:01:42,143 --> 00:01:46,690
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

36
00:01:46,690 --> 00:01:50,027
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

37
00:01:50,027 --> 00:01:53,822
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

38
00:01:53,822 --> 00:01:57,451
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

39
00:01:57,451 --> 00:02:02,081
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

40
00:02:02,081 --> 00:02:05,584
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

41
00:02:05,584 --> 00:02:09,504
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

42
00:02:09,504 --> 00:02:12,132
♪ NO, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
CHANGE MY MIND ♪

43
00:02:12,132 --> 00:02:15,260
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

44
00:02:15,260 --> 00:02:17,304
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

45
00:02:17,304 --> 00:02:20,390
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

46
00:02:20,390 --> 00:02:25,312
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

47
00:02:25,312 --> 00:02:28,315
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

48
00:02:28,315 --> 00:02:32,111
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

49
00:02:32,111 --> 00:02:35,739
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

50
00:02:35,739 --> 00:02:41,411
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

51
00:02:41,411 --> 00:02:43,246
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

52
00:02:43,246 --> 00:02:45,332
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

53
00:02:45,332 --> 00:02:49,252
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

54
00:02:49,252 --> 00:02:54,049
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

55
00:03:06,979 --> 00:03:08,647
I CAN'T WAIT TO GET BACK.

56
00:03:08,647 --> 00:03:10,899
TWO DAYS AGO, YOU COULDN'T WAIT
TO GET OFF THE SHIP.

57
00:03:10,899 --> 00:03:13,110
SIFTING THROUGH
A KLINGON GARBAGE DUMP --

58
00:03:13,110 --> 00:03:15,988
NOT MY IDEA OF EXPLORING
STRANGE NEW WORLDS.

59
00:03:15,988 --> 00:03:18,157
GETTING TIRED OF EXPLORATION,
ENSIGN?

60
00:03:18,157 --> 00:03:20,534
ALL THE PLANETS
STARTING TO LOOK ALIKE?

61
00:03:20,534 --> 00:03:21,910
NOT A CHANCE, SIR.

62
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:25,246
I DIDN'T THINK SO.
[ COUGHS ]

63
00:03:25,246 --> 00:03:28,375
I FEEL LIKE
I'M STILL BREATHING DIRT.

64
00:03:28,375 --> 00:03:30,127
<i>SHUTTLEPOD 1</i> TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

65
00:03:30,127 --> 00:03:33,005
Welcome back. How did your
treasure hunt turn out?

66
00:03:33,005 --> 00:03:34,923
WELL,
NOTHING WORTH BRINGING HOME.

67
00:03:34,923 --> 00:03:36,967
THE KLINGONS
MUST HAVE BEEN HERE YEARS AGO.

68
00:03:36,967 --> 00:03:38,510
ALL THEY LEFT WAS
AN OLD POWER CELL

69
00:03:38,510 --> 00:03:40,220
AND A BUNCH
OF EMPTY RATION PACKS.

70
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:41,388
AND A LATRINE.

71
00:03:41,388 --> 00:03:43,098
YEAH.

72
00:03:43,098 --> 00:03:45,392
A LONG, HOT SHOWER'S
LOOKING PRETTY GOOD.

73
00:03:45,392 --> 00:03:47,186
<i>SHUTTLEPOD 1</i> OUT.

74
00:03:47,186 --> 00:03:50,271
[ COUGHING ]

75
00:03:50,271 --> 00:03:51,356
COMMANDER?

76
00:03:51,356 --> 00:03:54,275
WHAT'S -- WHAT'S WRONG?

77
00:03:54,275 --> 00:03:56,528
TAKE OVER.

78
00:03:56,528 --> 00:03:58,072
GO TO DOCK.

79
00:03:58,072 --> 00:04:00,281
[ COUGHING ]

80
00:04:00,281 --> 00:04:02,743
<i>SHUTTLEPOD 1</i> TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

81
00:04:02,743 --> 00:04:06,538
I have a medical emergency.
Commander Tucker's collapsed.

82
00:04:06,538 --> 00:04:07,915
CAN YOU BRING THE SHUTTLEPOD IN?

83
00:04:07,915 --> 00:04:11,418
YES, SIR.
AT LEAST IN SIMULATIONS.

84
00:04:11,418 --> 00:04:13,628
SLOW AND STEADY, ENSIGN.

85
00:04:13,628 --> 00:04:15,547
I'LL SEE YOU IN DECON.

86
00:04:15,547 --> 00:04:17,424
UNDERSTOOD.

87
00:04:21,636 --> 00:04:23,471
CALL PHLOX.

88
00:04:23,471 --> 00:04:25,224
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

89
00:04:32,355 --> 00:04:33,440
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

90
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:35,525
TRIP, HOW YOU FEELING?

91
00:04:35,525 --> 00:04:38,987
OHH, LIKE I'VE BEEN GUT-PUNCHED
BY A TELLARITE.

92
00:04:38,987 --> 00:04:41,115
DOCTOR, SHOULD WE
START WITH THE BIO-GEL?

93
00:04:41,115 --> 00:04:43,158
NOT UNTIL WE KNOW
WHAT WE'RE DEALING WITH.

94
00:04:43,158 --> 00:04:44,743
THREE OTHER LANDING PARTIES
RETURNED FROM THE SURFACE

95
00:04:44,743 --> 00:04:46,120
WITH NO ILL EFFECTS.

96
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:48,413
WE NEED TO CHECK OUT
THE SHUTTLEPOD, TOO,

97
00:04:48,413 --> 00:04:51,374
SEE IF ANY OF ITS ENVIRONMENTAL
SYSTEMS WERE AT FAULT.

98
00:04:51,374 --> 00:04:52,667
I CAN DO THAT, CAPTAIN.

99
00:04:52,667 --> 00:04:54,795
I SHOULD HAVE
THOUGHT OF THAT MYSELF.

100
00:04:54,795 --> 00:04:57,256
STAY WHERE YOU ARE, TRIP.
PHLOX NEEDS BLOOD SAMPLES.

101
00:04:57,256 --> 00:04:58,506
HERE'S THE MED KITS.

102
00:05:02,302 --> 00:05:05,013
[ COUGHS ]

103
00:05:06,556 --> 00:05:08,642
HOSHI, WHAT IS IT?

104
00:05:08,642 --> 00:05:11,686
BEFORE COMMANDER TUCKER PASSED
OUT, HE STARTED COUGHING.

105
00:05:11,686 --> 00:05:14,106
ARE YOU FEELING
ANY OTHER SYMPTOMS?

106
00:05:17,276 --> 00:05:19,194
[ COUGHING ]

107
00:05:21,155 --> 00:05:23,782
I'M GONNA GUESS THAT'S A YES.

108
00:05:23,782 --> 00:05:25,742
I'LL PREPARE
ANTI-NAUSEA MEDICATION.

109
00:05:25,742 --> 00:05:28,328
GET ME THOSE BLOOD SAMPLES, HMM,
AS SOON AS YOU CAN.

110
00:05:30,371 --> 00:05:32,249
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

111
00:05:32,249 --> 00:05:33,625
ANYTHING?

112
00:05:33,625 --> 00:05:35,210
WHATEVER'S AFFLICTING THEM,

113
00:05:35,210 --> 00:05:37,087
IT'S NOT SHOWING UP
ON THE STANDARD SCANS.

114
00:05:37,087 --> 00:05:39,965
-DOESN'T SOUND GOOD.
-IT'S NOT.

115
00:05:39,965 --> 00:05:42,843
I STUDIED YOUR REPORT ON HOW
THE KLINGONS REACTED
TO THE INFECTION.

116
00:05:42,843 --> 00:05:44,636
THEIR RESPONSE WAS TYPICAL
FOR A SPECIES

117
00:05:44,636 --> 00:05:46,305
AT THEIR LEVEL
OF DEVELOPMENT.

118
00:05:46,305 --> 00:05:48,140
THE KLINGON COMMANDER

119
00:05:48,140 --> 00:05:50,017
DIDN'T LET HIS LANDING PARTY
BACK ON HIS SHIP.

120
00:05:50,017 --> 00:05:52,560
-YOUR POINT?
-CAPTAIN ARCHER DID.

121
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:55,730
CAPTAIN ARCHER'S DONE NOTHING
DIFFERENT FROM THE KLINGONS.

122
00:05:55,730 --> 00:05:58,192
THE LAUNCH BAY AND DECON CHAMBER

123
00:05:58,192 --> 00:06:00,401
ARE COMPLETELY ISOLATED
FROM THE REST OF THE SHIP.

124
00:06:00,401 --> 00:06:01,903
SO IT DOESN'T MATTER

125
00:06:01,903 --> 00:06:03,822
IF AN INFECTED LANDING PARTY
COMES ABOARD.

126
00:06:03,822 --> 00:06:05,949
PRECISELY.

127
00:06:05,949 --> 00:06:08,327
HUMANS DON'T WANT TO INTERACT
WITH DYING CREWMATES

128
00:06:08,327 --> 00:06:10,162
ANY MORE THAN KLINGONS DID.

129
00:06:10,162 --> 00:06:14,541
IF IT WAS LEFT TO ME, I'D STOP
OUR OBSERVATIONS IMMEDIATELY.

130
00:06:14,541 --> 00:06:16,710
WE HAVE NOTHING MORE TO LEARN
FROM HUMANS.

131
00:06:16,710 --> 00:06:18,212
OH, I DON'T KNOW.

132
00:06:18,212 --> 00:06:20,172
THEY'RE SHOWING CONCERN
FOR EACH OTHER.

133
00:06:20,172 --> 00:06:22,841
THE CARDASSIANS DID THAT WHEN
THEY WERE HERE, DIDN'T THEY?

134
00:06:22,841 --> 00:06:25,468
BUT IN THE END, THEY KILLED
THEIR INFECTED CREW,

135
00:06:25,468 --> 00:06:27,470
JUST AS THE KLINGONS DID.

136
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:30,598
THE ONLY DIFFERENCE IS THE TIME
IT TOOK TO REACH THAT DECISION.

137
00:06:30,598 --> 00:06:32,226
MAYBE THE HUMANS
WILL SURPRISE US.

138
00:06:32,226 --> 00:06:35,645
I'VE BEEN OBSERVING ALIENS
FOR 800 YEARS.

139
00:06:35,645 --> 00:06:36,897
I'VE YET TO BE SURPRISED.

140
00:06:36,897 --> 00:06:39,482
STILL,
WE SHOULD FOLLOW PROTOCOL.

141
00:06:39,482 --> 00:06:41,609
START QUESTIONING
THE INFECTED CREW.

142
00:06:41,609 --> 00:06:44,445
I'LL CHECK IN
WITH THE DOCTOR.

143
00:06:44,445 --> 00:06:45,989
OKAY.

144
00:06:45,989 --> 00:06:48,075
THIS IS FOR NAUSEA,

145
00:06:48,075 --> 00:06:51,119
MUSCLE PAIN,
AND A COUGH SUPPRESSANT.

146
00:06:51,119 --> 00:06:53,747
I'M NOT COUGHING ANYMORE.
NEITHER ARE YOU.

147
00:06:53,747 --> 00:06:55,332
MAYBE WE'RE GETTING BETTER.

148
00:06:55,332 --> 00:06:57,292
WELL, DOCTOR'S ORDERS.

149
00:06:58,626 --> 00:07:01,129
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]
COMMANDER.

150
00:07:01,129 --> 00:07:03,340
HOSHI. JUST WANTED TO SAY HI.

151
00:07:03,340 --> 00:07:06,425
UH, WE'RE A LITTLE BUSY
RIGHT NOW, TRAVIS.

152
00:07:06,425 --> 00:07:09,554
CAN YOU TELL ME
WHAT'S IN THE HYPOSPRAY?

153
00:07:09,554 --> 00:07:11,639
SOMETHING FOR OUR SYMPTOMS.

154
00:07:11,639 --> 00:07:14,059
YEAH. PHLOX DOESN'T KNOW
WHAT'S WRONG WITH US YET.

155
00:07:14,059 --> 00:07:18,646
HAVE EITHER OF YOU
FACED SERIOUS ILLNESS BEFORE?

156
00:07:20,982 --> 00:07:24,361
AREN'T YOU
SUPPOSED TO BE ON DUTY?

157
00:07:24,361 --> 00:07:26,487
I WAS CURIOUS TO KNOW
HOW YOU COMPARE THIS EXPERIENCE

158
00:07:26,487 --> 00:07:28,782
WITH OTHER ILLNESSES
YOU MIGHT HAVE CONTRACTED.

159
00:07:28,782 --> 00:07:33,703
TRAVIS...WE REALLY NEED
TO GET SOME SLEEP.

160
00:07:33,703 --> 00:07:35,789
I ONLY HAVE
A FEW MORE QUESTIONS.

161
00:07:35,789 --> 00:07:37,332
-THANKS FOR STOPPING BY.
-BUT --

162
00:07:52,513 --> 00:07:55,642
AH, LIEUTENANT REED.

163
00:07:55,642 --> 00:07:57,685
SOMETHING I CAN DO FOR YOU?

164
00:07:57,685 --> 00:07:59,854
HEADACHE.

165
00:07:59,854 --> 00:08:04,067
OF COURSE. YEAH, JUST A MOMENT.

166
00:08:04,067 --> 00:08:06,278
ARE THESE THE BLOOD TESTS

167
00:08:06,278 --> 00:08:08,780
FOR COMMANDER TUCKER
AND ENSIGN SATO?

168
00:08:08,780 --> 00:08:12,075
THAT'S CORRECT.

169
00:08:12,075 --> 00:08:15,536
HUH. I'M NOT DETECTING
ANY VASCULAR INVOLVEMENT.

170
00:08:15,536 --> 00:08:17,872
HMM?

171
00:08:17,872 --> 00:08:19,082
YOUR HEADACHE.

172
00:08:19,082 --> 00:08:21,835
NOT A BAD ONE, I TAKE IT?

173
00:08:21,835 --> 00:08:23,544
OH, NO, NOT YET.

174
00:08:23,544 --> 00:08:25,588
ALTHOUGH IT FEELS
LIKE IT COULD GET WORSE.

175
00:08:25,588 --> 00:08:28,842
PREVENTATIVE MEASURE.
A LOT TO DO TODAY.

176
00:08:28,842 --> 00:08:30,802
MILD ANALGESIC IT IS.

177
00:08:30,802 --> 00:08:32,595
AH.

178
00:08:32,595 --> 00:08:35,140
DOCTOR, I'M CURIOUS TO KNOW
HOW YOU THINK

179
00:08:35,140 --> 00:08:37,767
THESE TESTS WILL HELP YOU
DEVELOP AN EFFECTIVE TREATMENT.

180
00:08:37,767 --> 00:08:39,102
SO AM I.

181
00:08:39,102 --> 00:08:40,854
I MEAN, ARE YOU
APPROACHING THIS STRICTLY

182
00:08:40,854 --> 00:08:42,230
ON A SYMPTOMATIC LEVEL,

183
00:08:42,230 --> 00:08:44,191
OR DO YOU BELIEVE
THERE'S ANY SIMILARITY

184
00:08:44,191 --> 00:08:46,818
TO OTHER CONDITIONS
YOU'VE SEEN IN THE PAST?

185
00:08:46,818 --> 00:08:48,653
[ CHUCKLES ]

186
00:08:48,653 --> 00:08:52,449
LIEUTENANT, I BELIEVE I CAN
PUT YOUR MIND AT EASE.

187
00:08:54,409 --> 00:08:57,287
IF YOUR COLLEAGUES HAVE RETURNED
WITH A CONTAGIOUS ILLNESS,

188
00:08:57,287 --> 00:08:59,206
THERE IS NO WAY IT CAN SPREAD
TO THE REST OF THE SHIP.

189
00:08:59,206 --> 00:09:00,874
WE ARE ALL QUITE SAFE.

190
00:09:00,874 --> 00:09:02,334
I'M NOT WORRIED
ABOUT THAT, NO.

191
00:09:02,334 --> 00:09:04,002
I'M INTERESTED
IN THE METHODOLOGY --

192
00:09:04,002 --> 00:09:07,130
OUT! OUT! OUT!
I HAVE A LOT TO DO AS WELL.

193
00:09:07,130 --> 00:09:08,423
HMM?

194
00:09:13,928 --> 00:09:16,931
YOU EVER SEE
"THE ANDROMEDA STRAIN"?

195
00:09:16,931 --> 00:09:18,183
STRAIN OF WHAT?

196
00:09:18,183 --> 00:09:22,562
IT'S A MOVIE,
MID-20th CENTURY.

197
00:09:22,562 --> 00:09:23,771
LET ME GUESS.

198
00:09:23,771 --> 00:09:25,773
DR. ANDROMEDA
BUILDS A MONSTER,

199
00:09:25,773 --> 00:09:28,776
AND IT KILLS HIM
IN THE END.

200
00:09:28,776 --> 00:09:31,946
IT'S ABOUT
AN EXTRATERRESTRIAL DISEASE.

201
00:09:31,946 --> 00:09:33,365
ALL YOUR MOVIES ARE THE SAME.

202
00:09:33,365 --> 00:09:35,116
I CAN'T KEEP
THE STORIES STRAIGHT.

203
00:09:35,116 --> 00:09:39,829
THIS REMINDS ME OF MY DORM ROOM
AT STARFLEET TRAINING.

204
00:09:39,829 --> 00:09:42,790
GOT INTO A LOT OF TROUBLE
AT OLD STC.

205
00:09:44,792 --> 00:09:46,211
I GOT KICKED OUT.

206
00:09:51,758 --> 00:09:53,968
WELL, YOU CAN'T STOP THERE.

207
00:09:53,968 --> 00:09:57,847
IN MY SECOND MONTH, I...

208
00:09:57,847 --> 00:10:00,850
I HAD A DIFFERENCE OF OPINION
WITH THE COMPANY COMMANDER.

209
00:10:04,104 --> 00:10:06,856
I BROKE HIS ARM.

210
00:10:08,442 --> 00:10:09,943
CAN I ASK WHY?

211
00:10:09,943 --> 00:10:12,904
POKER.

212
00:10:12,904 --> 00:10:15,073
YOU BROKE HIS ARM PLAYING CARDS?

213
00:10:15,073 --> 00:10:17,367
HE TRIED TO SHUT DOWN A GAME
I WAS RUNNING

214
00:10:17,367 --> 00:10:21,455
FOR SOME OF THE RECRUITS AND
A COUPLE OF THE TRAINING STAFF.

215
00:10:21,455 --> 00:10:23,957
HOLD ON.

216
00:10:23,957 --> 00:10:27,710
YOU RAN A FLOATING
POKER GAME AT STC?

217
00:10:27,710 --> 00:10:29,796
THE WAY THE REGULATIONS
ARE WORDED,

218
00:10:29,796 --> 00:10:31,672
GAMBLING WAS
AN HONOR VIOLATION

219
00:10:31,672 --> 00:10:34,842
ONLY IF IT TOOK PLACE
DURING DUTY HOURS.

220
00:10:34,842 --> 00:10:36,219
SO I RAN THE GAME
ON WEEKENDS.

221
00:10:36,219 --> 00:10:38,513
ONE NIGHT
MY C.C. SHOWED UP,

222
00:10:38,513 --> 00:10:42,809
TRIED TO SWEEP ALL THE CHIPS
OFF THE TABLE, AND I --

223
00:10:42,809 --> 00:10:45,103
WELL, I HAVE A BLACK BELT
IN AIKIDO.

224
00:10:46,854 --> 00:10:49,816
I THINK HE WAS JUST UPSET THAT
I HADN'T INVITED HIM TO PLAY.

225
00:10:49,816 --> 00:10:51,692
WHAT HAPPENED?

226
00:10:53,987 --> 00:10:56,739
I GOT A BAD-CONDUCT DISCHARGE.

227
00:10:58,866 --> 00:11:01,620
HOW THE HELL DID YOU END UP
ON<i> ENTERPRISE?</i>

228
00:11:01,620 --> 00:11:04,289
STARFLEET NEEDED
LANGUAGE SPECIALISTS

229
00:11:04,289 --> 00:11:06,458
MORE THAN THEY NEEDED TO MAKE
AN EXAMPLE OUT OF ME.

230
00:11:06,458 --> 00:11:09,169
THEY LET ME BACK IN
ON PROBATION,

231
00:11:09,169 --> 00:11:14,257
AND [SIGHS] HERE I AM.

232
00:11:14,257 --> 00:11:17,260
HUH.

233
00:11:17,260 --> 00:11:20,639
THE CLOSEST CLASSIFICATION
IT MATCHES IS A VIRUS.

234
00:11:20,639 --> 00:11:22,056
HIGHLY CONTAGIOUS.

235
00:11:22,056 --> 00:11:24,476
SILICON-BASED.

236
00:11:25,935 --> 00:11:27,437
THIS IS AN M-CLASS PLANET.

237
00:11:27,437 --> 00:11:30,440
ALL LIFE-FORMS DOWN THERE
SHOULD BE CARBON-BASED.

238
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:32,900
I CAN ONLY SURMISE
THE VIRUS WAS BROUGHT HERE,

239
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:35,529
PERHAPS BY A METEORITE,
WHICH COULD EXPLAIN WHY

240
00:11:35,529 --> 00:11:37,572
ONLY ONE OF OUR LANDING PARTIES
ENCOUNTERED IT.

241
00:11:37,572 --> 00:11:38,906
IS THERE A TREATMENT?

242
00:11:38,906 --> 00:11:40,867
THERE'S NO RECORD
OF ANYTHING LIKE IT

243
00:11:40,867 --> 00:11:42,285
IN THE DENOBULAN DATABASE.

244
00:11:43,870 --> 00:11:45,746
THEN IT'S UP TO YOU.

245
00:11:45,746 --> 00:11:47,415
I'LL DO ALL I CAN, CAPTAIN,

246
00:11:47,415 --> 00:11:50,585
BUT AT THE RATE THE PATHOGEN
IS REPRODUCING,

247
00:11:50,585 --> 00:11:53,004
COMMANDER TUCKER
AND ENSIGN SATO

248
00:11:53,004 --> 00:11:54,964
HAVE LESS THAN FIVE HOURS
TO LIVE.

249
00:12:03,890 --> 00:12:07,018
THE DOCTOR
IDENTIFIED THE PATHOGEN.

250
00:12:07,018 --> 00:12:08,102
AH.

251
00:12:08,102 --> 00:12:11,939
THAT HAPPENS 37% OF THE TIME.

252
00:12:11,939 --> 00:12:13,274
BUT NO ONE'S MADE THE DECISION

253
00:12:13,274 --> 00:12:15,902
TO ABANDON
THE INFECTED CREWMEMBERS.

254
00:12:15,902 --> 00:12:19,531
THEN THIS WILL LIKELY BE ONE
OF THE TIMES WHEN EVERYONE DIES.

255
00:12:21,616 --> 00:12:22,701
HMM.

256
00:12:34,588 --> 00:12:36,923
-[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]
-TRAVIS.

257
00:12:36,923 --> 00:12:38,757
[ SIGHS ]
IF THAT'S YOU AGAIN...

258
00:12:38,757 --> 00:12:40,468
IT'S ME.

259
00:12:43,471 --> 00:12:45,973
NEXT TIME I ASK
TO GO ON A LANDING PARTY,

260
00:12:45,973 --> 00:12:48,476
TALK ME OUT OF IT, OKAY?

261
00:12:48,476 --> 00:12:51,062
YOU'RE USUALLY TOO STUBBORN
TO BE TALKED OUT OF ANYTHING.

262
00:12:51,062 --> 00:12:54,107
BUT I'LL DO MY BEST.

263
00:12:57,776 --> 00:13:00,154
-HOW'S HOSHI?
-SLEEPING.

264
00:13:00,154 --> 00:13:02,365
WHATEVER PHLOX GAVE US,

265
00:13:02,365 --> 00:13:04,325
AT LEAST IT'S HELPING
WITH THE PAIN.

266
00:13:04,325 --> 00:13:06,994
PHLOX IDENTIFIED WHAT'S CAUSING
ALL THE TROUBLE --

267
00:13:06,994 --> 00:13:10,331
A SILICON-BASED VIRUS.

268
00:13:10,331 --> 00:13:13,126
I DON'T SUPPOSE HE'S ON HIS WAY
OVER HERE WITH THE CURE.

269
00:13:13,126 --> 00:13:16,170
HE'S WORKING ON IT.

270
00:13:16,170 --> 00:13:17,796
SO IS T'POL.

271
00:13:17,796 --> 00:13:20,717
SO THERE IS NO CURE.

272
00:13:20,717 --> 00:13:22,302
NOT YET.

273
00:13:22,302 --> 00:13:26,389
I'M GETTING THE IDEA
YOU'RE UP AGAINST A DEADLINE.

274
00:13:26,389 --> 00:13:28,224
IF YOU MEAN
HOW MUCH TIME DO YOU HAVE,

275
00:13:28,224 --> 00:13:30,477
IT'S TOO EARLY FOR
THAT KIND OF TALK.

276
00:13:30,477 --> 00:13:33,605
YOUR OWN IMMUNE SYSTEM
COULD KNOCK THIS THING OUT.

277
00:13:33,605 --> 00:13:38,025
I REMEMBER EXOBIOLOGY 101,
CAPTAIN.

278
00:13:38,025 --> 00:13:40,027
HUMANS ARE CARBON-BASED.

279
00:13:40,027 --> 00:13:44,073
OUR IMMUNE SYSTEM
CAN'T FIGHT SILICON.

280
00:13:44,073 --> 00:13:46,033
DON'T YOU GIVE UP ON ME.

281
00:13:47,826 --> 00:13:50,997
THERE'S STILL A BUNCH OF PLANETS
OUT THERE WE HAVEN'T SEEN.

282
00:13:53,166 --> 00:13:54,709
GET SOME REST.

283
00:13:57,962 --> 00:13:59,172
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

284
00:14:06,137 --> 00:14:08,348
WE'RE LOOKING FOR SIGNS
OF ELEVATED INTELLIGENCE

285
00:14:08,348 --> 00:14:10,099
IN THE SPECIES WE OBSERVE.

286
00:14:10,099 --> 00:14:12,059
RATIONAL INTELLIGENCE, YES,

287
00:14:12,059 --> 00:14:13,936
WHICH ARCHER HAS
NOT DEMONSTRATED.

288
00:14:13,936 --> 00:14:15,854
THE LONGER THE INFECTED CREW
REMAIN ONBOARD,

289
00:14:15,854 --> 00:14:17,774
THE GREATER THE RISK
THAT QUARANTINE WILL FAIL.

290
00:14:17,774 --> 00:14:21,027
I'M SURE CAPTAIN ARCHER KNOWS
EXACTLY WHAT THE RISK IS.

291
00:14:21,027 --> 00:14:23,571
MAYBE IT'S NOT AS IMPORTANT
TO HIM AS STANDING BY HIS CREW.

292
00:14:23,571 --> 00:14:26,073
IT'S JUST AS PROBABLE
THAT HE HASN'T REALIZED

293
00:14:26,073 --> 00:14:28,326
HOW HOPELESS THE SITUATION IS.

294
00:14:28,326 --> 00:14:31,078
THERE'S A WAY TO BE SURE.

295
00:14:34,999 --> 00:14:38,628
WE CHOSE THE HELMSMAN AND THE
ARMORY OFFICER FOR GOOD REASON.

296
00:14:38,628 --> 00:14:40,672
THEY'RE BOTH STATIONED
ON THE BRIDGE,

297
00:14:40,672 --> 00:14:43,842
YET NEITHER PLAYS A CRITICAL
ROLE IN A MEDICAL EMERGENCY.

298
00:14:43,842 --> 00:14:47,094
WHICH IS WHY WE SHOULD
INHABIT THE DOCTOR AND
THE SCIENCE OFFICER.

299
00:14:47,094 --> 00:14:49,930
ARCHER RELIES ON THEIR FINDINGS
TO MAKE HIS DECISIONS.

300
00:14:49,930 --> 00:14:52,266
WE COULD WITNESS THAT
AS IT HAPPENS.

301
00:14:52,266 --> 00:14:54,310
THE MORE PEOPLE WE INHABIT,

302
00:14:54,310 --> 00:14:57,021
THE GREATER THE CHANCE THAT WE
WILL INADVERTENTLY INTERFERE.

303
00:14:57,021 --> 00:15:01,442
THE MORE PEOPLE WE INHABIT, THE
MORE WE'LL BE ABLE TO OBSERVE.

304
00:15:03,236 --> 00:15:06,197
HOW MANY LANGUAGES
CAN YOU SPEAK?

305
00:15:06,197 --> 00:15:08,282
THAT'S NOT HOW IT WORKS.

306
00:15:08,282 --> 00:15:10,117
THERE ARE
A LOT OF COMMON PATTERNS.

307
00:15:10,117 --> 00:15:12,036
I'M JUST GOOD
AT HEARING THEM, THAT'S ALL.

308
00:15:12,036 --> 00:15:13,246
GOOD?

309
00:15:13,246 --> 00:15:15,331
YOU'RE A GENIUS,

310
00:15:15,331 --> 00:15:17,709
THE WAY YOU CAN PICK UP
AN ALIEN LANGUAGE

311
00:15:17,709 --> 00:15:21,003
YOU'VE NEVER HEARD BEFORE AND
START SPOUTING IT BACK TO THEM.

312
00:15:21,003 --> 00:15:24,632
I GOT TO TELL YOU, I'VE ALWAYS
BEEN JEALOUS YOU CAN DO THAT.

313
00:15:24,632 --> 00:15:26,926
I WISH I COULD FIX WARP ENGINES

314
00:15:26,926 --> 00:15:30,054
WITH DUCT TAPE
AND A POCKETKNIFE.

315
00:15:30,054 --> 00:15:34,601
IT -- IT'S...A BIT MORE
COMPLICATED THAN THAT.

316
00:15:34,601 --> 00:15:36,185
SOMETIMES.

317
00:15:36,185 --> 00:15:39,146
SERIOUSLY.

318
00:15:39,146 --> 00:15:40,940
ENGINEERING,
BUILDING THINGS --

319
00:15:40,940 --> 00:15:42,983
HAVE YOU ALWAYS
BEEN GOOD AT THAT?

320
00:15:42,983 --> 00:15:46,028
MM...WHEN I WAS A KID,

321
00:15:46,028 --> 00:15:48,615
NOT SO GOOD AT BUILDING.

322
00:15:48,615 --> 00:15:52,577
BUT I WAS A TERROR WHEN IT CAME
TO TAKING THINGS APART.

323
00:15:52,577 --> 00:15:55,037
MY FOLKS USED TO PUT
ALL OUR KITCHEN APPLIANCES

324
00:15:55,037 --> 00:15:56,873
ON THE HIGHEST SHELVES.

325
00:15:56,873 --> 00:16:01,085
ONE THANKSGIVING, I HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT I WAS THINKING, BUT, UM,

326
00:16:01,085 --> 00:16:02,629
I REMOVED EVERY SCREW

327
00:16:02,629 --> 00:16:06,591
FROM THIS BIG DINING-ROOM TABLE
WE HAD.

328
00:16:06,591 --> 00:16:09,969
IT WAS SO OLD, THE WOOD
SORT OF STUCK TOGETHER.

329
00:16:09,969 --> 00:16:12,263
SO IT STAYED STANDING...

330
00:16:12,263 --> 00:16:14,056
UNTIL MY DAD
PUT THE TURKEY DOWN.

331
00:16:14,056 --> 00:16:15,558
[ CHUCKLES ]

332
00:16:15,558 --> 00:16:17,852
I SPENT THE NEXT MONTH
IN MY ROOM.

333
00:16:17,852 --> 00:16:18,853
HOW OLD WERE YOU?

334
00:16:18,853 --> 00:16:22,064
OH...24, 25.

335
00:16:22,064 --> 00:16:23,441
[ CHUCKLES ]

336
00:16:33,075 --> 00:16:34,869
HOW LONG HAVE THEY BEEN THERE?

337
00:16:34,869 --> 00:16:36,830
WE DIDN'T SEE YOU THERE.

338
00:16:36,830 --> 00:16:39,666
-[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]
-WE DIDN'T WANT
TO INTERRUPT YOU.

339
00:16:39,666 --> 00:16:42,293
HOW'S THE RESEARCH COMING?

340
00:16:42,293 --> 00:16:44,545
WE'RE WAITING ON
NEW TEST RESULTS.

341
00:16:44,545 --> 00:16:47,381
WE THOUGHT WE'D SEE
HOW YOU TWO WERE PROGRESSING.

342
00:16:47,381 --> 00:16:50,468
YOU'RE THE ONES WITH
THE MEDICAL SCANNERS.

343
00:16:50,468 --> 00:16:54,555
WE WERE MORE INTERESTED IN
DISCUSSING YOUR STATE OF MIND.

344
00:16:54,555 --> 00:16:56,098
[ SIGHS ]

345
00:16:56,098 --> 00:16:58,768
LOOK, IF YOU REALLY WANT
TO KNOW HOW WE FEEL,

346
00:16:58,768 --> 00:17:01,980
WE'D BE A LOT BETTER KNOWING
YOU TWO WERE BACK IN SICKBAY

347
00:17:01,980 --> 00:17:04,023
WORKING ON THE CURE FOR THIS.

348
00:17:04,023 --> 00:17:07,777
OF COURSE.
WE'RE GOING THERE NOW.

349
00:17:09,904 --> 00:17:12,907
COMMANDER, ENSIGN.

350
00:17:18,913 --> 00:17:20,748
THEY BOTH CAME TO SEE US.

351
00:17:20,748 --> 00:17:23,376
MAYBE THAT MEANS
THEY'RE ALMOST FINISHED.

352
00:17:23,376 --> 00:17:27,087
YEAH, UNLESS THERE'S
NOTHING MORE THEY CAN DO.

353
00:17:27,087 --> 00:17:30,884
THEY'RE VERY BRAVE,
THE WAY THEY'RE FACING DEATH.

354
00:17:30,884 --> 00:17:34,512
THEIR COURAGE ISN'T AT QUESTION.
THEIR INTELLIGENCE IS.

355
00:17:34,512 --> 00:17:36,263
YOU WANT THE HUMANS TO FAIL.

356
00:17:36,263 --> 00:17:38,349
THIS ISN'T A COMPETITION.

357
00:17:38,349 --> 00:17:40,560
EITHER A SPECIES'
INTELLIGENCE IS DEVELOPED

358
00:17:40,560 --> 00:17:42,979
ENOUGH FOR FIRST CONTACT,
OR IT ISN'T.

359
00:17:42,979 --> 00:17:45,899
PERHAPS WE SHOULD CONSIDER
OTHER QUALITIES IN MAKING
OUR DECISION.

360
00:17:45,899 --> 00:17:49,027
THIS IS THE MEASURE
WE HAVE USED FOR 10,000 YEARS.

361
00:17:49,027 --> 00:17:51,111
IT'S NOT OUR RESPONSIBILITY
TO CHANGE IT.

362
00:17:51,111 --> 00:17:53,573
THEN WHOSE RESPONSIBILITY
IS IT?

363
00:17:53,573 --> 00:17:57,243
THERE. IF PHLOX IS RIGHT
ABOUT THE VIRUS COMING
HERE ON A METEORITE,

364
00:17:57,243 --> 00:17:59,620
THAT CRATER
MIGHT BE THE SOURCE OF IT,

365
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:03,457
WHICH MEANS
THE KLINGONS AT THIS CAMPSITE
MUST HAVE BEEN INFECTED, TOO.

366
00:18:03,457 --> 00:18:05,752
SET UP A PRIORITY CHANNEL
TO STARFLEET COMMAND.

367
00:18:05,752 --> 00:18:08,128
WE NEED TO FIND OUT
WHICH KLINGON SHIP
EXPLORED THIS WORLD,

368
00:18:08,128 --> 00:18:10,172
AND WHETHER OR NOT
THEY DEVELOPED A CURE.

369
00:18:10,172 --> 00:18:12,759
RIGHT AWAY, SIR.

370
00:18:12,759 --> 00:18:14,343
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

371
00:18:14,343 --> 00:18:16,846
THOSE ARE THE NEW TEST RESULTS
MY HOST IS WAITING FOR.

372
00:18:16,846 --> 00:18:21,392
WE SHOULD LEAVE THESE CREATURES
TO THEIR WORK UNDISTURBED.

373
00:18:21,392 --> 00:18:25,855
THE HELMSMAN AND THE ARMORY
OFFICER ARE BACK ON THE BRIDGE.

374
00:18:33,237 --> 00:18:37,033
THE ALTERED IMMUNE RECEPTORS
WEREN'T EFFECTIVE.

375
00:18:38,826 --> 00:18:42,872
THIS COULD INDICATE THE VIRUS IS
SENSITIVE TO IONIZING RADIATION.

376
00:18:44,916 --> 00:18:49,128
AT LEVELS THAT WOULD BE FATAL
TO HUMANS, BUT IT'S A START.

377
00:18:49,128 --> 00:18:51,380
I'LL PREPARE NEW SAMPLES
FOR TESTING.

378
00:18:54,842 --> 00:18:57,177
[ PANTING ]

379
00:18:57,177 --> 00:19:00,098
[ SPEAKING JAPANESE ]

380
00:19:00,098 --> 00:19:01,223
HOSHI.

381
00:19:01,223 --> 00:19:03,017
[ SPEAKING GERMAN ]

382
00:19:03,017 --> 00:19:05,352
-[ SPEAKING FRENCH ]
-HOSHI, WAKE UP!

383
00:19:05,352 --> 00:19:08,064
[ PANTING ]

384
00:19:08,064 --> 00:19:10,566
I WAS BACK IN BRAZIL...

385
00:19:10,566 --> 00:19:15,989
WHERE...THE SHUTTLE WAS COMING

386
00:19:15,989 --> 00:19:17,448
TO TAKE ME TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

387
00:19:17,448 --> 00:19:19,533
THAT'S WHERE WE ARE.

388
00:19:27,792 --> 00:19:32,088
CAPTAIN ARCHER NEEDED ME EARLY.

389
00:19:32,088 --> 00:19:35,549
I DIDN'T GET THE CHANCE TO SAY
GOODBYE TO MY STUDENTS.

390
00:19:38,845 --> 00:19:40,554
YOU'LL SEE THEM AGAIN.

391
00:19:45,267 --> 00:19:46,978
I'VE HEARD FROM STARFLEET.

392
00:19:46,978 --> 00:19:49,897
THEY'RE WORKING
THROUGH DIPLOMATIC CHANNELS

393
00:19:49,897 --> 00:19:51,231
TO CONTACT THE KLINGONS,

394
00:19:51,231 --> 00:19:53,275
BUT IT MIGHT NOT
BE NECESSARY.

395
00:19:53,275 --> 00:19:56,737
THIS SPECTROGRAPH
IDENTIFIES A KLINGON ALLOY.

396
00:19:56,737 --> 00:19:59,323
THAT'S THE SIGNATURE
OF STANDARD HULL PLATING.

397
00:19:59,323 --> 00:20:03,744
I FOUND IT...HERE.

398
00:20:03,744 --> 00:20:06,706
YOU'VE DETECTED
A DEBRIS CLOUD IN ORBIT.

399
00:20:06,706 --> 00:20:09,167
IT'S WHAT'S LEFT OF
A KLINGON SHUTTLECRAFT --

400
00:20:09,167 --> 00:20:11,794
THEIR RESPONSE
TO AN INFECTED LANDING PARTY.

401
00:20:11,794 --> 00:20:14,172
THE COMMANDER
KILLED HIS OWN SHUTTLE CREW.

402
00:20:14,172 --> 00:20:16,549
THEY DIDN'T EVEN PLEAD
FOR MERCY.

403
00:20:17,717 --> 00:20:20,219
I MEAN,
THEY WOULDN'T, WOULD THEY,

404
00:20:20,219 --> 00:20:22,471
BEING KLINGON?

405
00:20:22,471 --> 00:20:25,391
CAPTAIN, DOES KNOWING WHAT THE
KLINGONS DID HELP US AT ALL?

406
00:20:25,391 --> 00:20:28,186
AT LEAST WE KNOW
WE DON'T HAVE TO BOTHER

407
00:20:28,186 --> 00:20:30,104
ASKING THEM IF
THEY HAVE A CURE.

408
00:20:30,104 --> 00:20:34,192
BUT IF THEY HAD DEVELOPED ONE,
YOU'D ASK THEM FOR IT, RIGHT?

409
00:20:36,152 --> 00:20:38,029
ON BENDED KNEE.

410
00:20:42,033 --> 00:20:45,078
[ SPEAKING SPANISH ]

411
00:20:45,078 --> 00:20:48,789
[ COMPUTER BEEPING ]

412
00:20:48,789 --> 00:20:50,374
HOSHI.

413
00:20:51,876 --> 00:20:54,294
WE'RE IN QUARANTINE
FOR A REASON.

414
00:20:54,294 --> 00:20:56,630
[ SPEAKING KLINGON ]

415
00:20:56,630 --> 00:21:00,551
I HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT YOU'RE SAYING,

416
00:21:00,551 --> 00:21:02,803
BUT YOU CAN'T
BREAK THE LOCKOUT CODE.

417
00:21:02,803 --> 00:21:06,515
MATH IS JUST ANOTHER LANGUAGE.

418
00:21:06,515 --> 00:21:10,269
-[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]
-[ ALARM SOUNDING ]

419
00:21:10,269 --> 00:21:12,688
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]
QUARANTINE BREACH ON "D" DECK.

420
00:21:14,356 --> 00:21:16,275
THE DECON CHAMBER
HAS BEEN UNSEALED.

421
00:21:25,993 --> 00:21:27,578
[ GASPING ]

422
00:21:39,381 --> 00:21:41,717
SOMEONE'S OVERRIDING
THE SAFETY INTERLOCKS.

423
00:21:41,717 --> 00:21:44,637
SHUT DOWN ALL POWER TO "D" DECK.
I WANT THOSE DOORS SEALED.

424
00:21:48,224 --> 00:21:50,476
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

425
00:21:52,228 --> 00:21:55,689
HOSHI, YOU HAVE TO STOP.

426
00:21:55,689 --> 00:21:59,193
THAT'S AN AIRLOCK.
YOU OPEN THOSE DOORS, WE DIE.

427
00:21:59,193 --> 00:22:01,361
[ SPEAKING RUSSIAN ]

428
00:22:01,361 --> 00:22:03,322
[ SIGHS ] HOSHI, COME ON.

429
00:22:03,322 --> 00:22:05,283
I NEED TO TELL THEM...

430
00:22:05,283 --> 00:22:07,785
[ BOTH GRUNT ]

431
00:22:10,537 --> 00:22:12,665
[ GASPING ]

432
00:22:12,665 --> 00:22:15,168
...WHILE THERE'S STILL TIME.

433
00:22:15,168 --> 00:22:17,711
THE CAPTAIN WON'T LET US DOWN.

434
00:22:42,360 --> 00:22:43,361
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

435
00:22:43,361 --> 00:22:45,990
TRIP TO, UH...

436
00:22:48,117 --> 00:22:50,494
[ SIGHS ]
WHOEVER'S OUT THERE.

437
00:22:52,538 --> 00:22:54,456
WE'RE BACK.

438
00:22:54,456 --> 00:22:56,500
COMMANDER, I WANT YOU
TO SET YOUR HYPOSPRAY

439
00:22:56,500 --> 00:22:59,170
FOR THREE UNITS OF SONAMBUTRIL.

440
00:23:02,631 --> 00:23:04,382
<i>THAT COULD DROP A HORSE.</i>

441
00:23:04,382 --> 00:23:06,635
WE CAN'T RISK HOSHI
WANDERING OFF AGAIN,

442
00:23:06,635 --> 00:23:08,679
ESPECIALLY SINCE
IT SEEMS SHE CAN OVERRIDE

443
00:23:08,679 --> 00:23:11,224
EVERY SECURITY SAFEGUARD
ON<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

444
00:23:13,893 --> 00:23:18,438
YEAH, SHE'S...FULL
OF SURPRISES TODAY.

445
00:23:42,171 --> 00:23:44,882
SWEET DREAMS, HOUDINI.

446
00:23:44,882 --> 00:23:46,050
[ SIGHS ]

447
00:23:48,552 --> 00:23:49,595
<i>ANYTHING ELSE?</i>

448
00:23:49,595 --> 00:23:52,390
IT'S YOUR TURN, TRIP.

449
00:23:52,390 --> 00:23:54,267
<i>COME ON, CAPTAIN.</i>

450
00:23:54,267 --> 00:23:57,811
COMMANDER, THE VIRUS
IS INCOMPATIBLE WITH
CARBON-BASED LIFE.

451
00:23:57,811 --> 00:24:00,106
IT'S ATTACKING YOUR BODIES
IN WAYS I CAN'T PREDICT.

452
00:24:00,106 --> 00:24:02,358
<i>YOU THINK I'M GONNA</i>
<i>WANDER OFF, TOO,</i>

453
00:24:02,358 --> 00:24:04,484
<i>START OPENING THE WRONG DOORS?</i>

454
00:24:04,484 --> 00:24:05,569
NOT IF YOU'RE SEDATED.

455
00:24:05,569 --> 00:24:06,946
SORRY, TRIP.

456
00:24:06,946 --> 00:24:08,572
[ SIGHS ]

457
00:24:16,622 --> 00:24:18,207
COMMANDER.

458
00:24:20,376 --> 00:24:24,046
I'M JUST WONDERING IF EITHER ONE
OF US WILL EVER WAKE UP AGAIN.

459
00:24:28,466 --> 00:24:30,428
<i>YOU SHOULD LIE DOWN</i>
<i>RIGHT AWAY.</i>

460
00:24:30,428 --> 00:24:31,804
I WON'T ARGUE WITH THAT.

461
00:24:36,725 --> 00:24:39,895
HOW CLOSE ARE YOU
TO STOPPING THIS?

462
00:24:39,895 --> 00:24:43,023
T'POL AND I HAVE ISOLATED A
SPECIFIC FREQUENCY OF RADIATION

463
00:24:43,023 --> 00:24:45,359
THAT DISRUPTS THE SILICON MATRIX
OF THE VIRUS.

464
00:24:45,359 --> 00:24:46,986
SOUNDS PROMISING.

465
00:24:46,986 --> 00:24:50,114
UNFORTUNATELY, THE DOSAGE
REQUIRED WOULD BE LETHAL.

466
00:24:51,740 --> 00:24:53,659
THERE'S GOT TO BE
SOME KIND OF A TRADEOFF --

467
00:24:53,659 --> 00:24:55,328
A WAY TO PRODUCE
ENOUGH RADIATION

468
00:24:55,328 --> 00:24:58,372
TO SLOW DOWN THE VIRUS
WITHOUT KILLING THE PATIENT.

469
00:24:58,372 --> 00:25:00,082
THAT'S WHAT I'M WORKING ON.

470
00:25:00,082 --> 00:25:01,959
WORK FASTER.

471
00:25:12,552 --> 00:25:15,513
WE CAN STOP WHAT THIS VIRUS
IS DOING TO THEM.

472
00:25:15,513 --> 00:25:17,515
THAT'S NOT WHY WE'RE HERE.

473
00:25:17,515 --> 00:25:19,768
WE CAME TO OBSERVE
THEIR RESPONSE

474
00:25:19,768 --> 00:25:23,147
TO THE UNEXPECTED,
NOT TO WATCH THEM SUFFER.

475
00:25:23,147 --> 00:25:26,775
THIS IS NOT THE PLACE
TO BE HAVING THIS DISCUSSION.

476
00:25:26,775 --> 00:25:30,321
I KNOW WHERE WE CAN TALK
UNDISTURBED.

477
00:25:35,326 --> 00:25:37,286
[ SIGHS ]

478
00:25:37,286 --> 00:25:40,164
THE SENSATIONS IN THIS HOST
ARE DIFFERENT FROM THE OTHERS.

479
00:25:40,164 --> 00:25:43,541
I'M EXPERIENCING PHYSICAL PAIN.

480
00:25:43,541 --> 00:25:46,045
SO AM I.

481
00:25:46,045 --> 00:25:50,132
WHY SHOULD ANY SPECIES
HAVE TO ENDURE THIS WEAKNESS?

482
00:25:50,132 --> 00:25:53,010
BECAUSE THE DESIRE TO OVERCOME
IT WILL SPUR THEM TO MOVE

483
00:25:53,010 --> 00:25:55,388
BEYOND THE LIMITATIONS
OF THE PHYSICAL WORLD.

484
00:25:55,388 --> 00:25:58,391
MAYBE THAT ISN'T TRUE
FOR ALL SPECIES.

485
00:25:58,391 --> 00:25:59,683
IT WAS TRUE FOR US.

486
00:26:05,356 --> 00:26:08,317
YOU CAN'T BE AWAKE.

487
00:26:10,610 --> 00:26:13,197
NOT WITH THAT MUCH SONAMBUTRIL.

488
00:26:15,324 --> 00:26:17,410
<i>OUR ANCESTORS</i>
<i>WERE PHYSICAL BEINGS.</i>

489
00:26:17,410 --> 00:26:19,245
<i>WELL, WHAT WORKED FOR US</i>
<i>MIGHT NOT WORK FOR EVERYONE.</i>

490
00:26:19,245 --> 00:26:21,414
<i>HUMANS HAVE</i>
<i>DIFFERENT QUALITIES.</i>

491
00:26:21,414 --> 00:26:23,040
<i>NOTHING I HAVEN'T</i>
<i>SEEN BEFORE.</i>

492
00:26:23,040 --> 00:26:25,042
<i>WHAT DO YOU HAVE</i>
<i>AGAINST THIS SPECIES?</i>

493
00:26:25,042 --> 00:26:27,044
<i>WHAT DISTURBS ME</i>
<i>MOST ABOUT THE HUMANS</i>

494
00:26:27,044 --> 00:26:28,754
<i>IS THEIR CAPACITY</i>
<i>FOR VIOLENCE.</i>

495
00:26:28,754 --> 00:26:30,548
EXTRAORDINARY.

496
00:26:30,548 --> 00:26:31,757
KLINGONS EMBRACE VIOLENCE.

497
00:26:31,757 --> 00:26:33,633
THE HUMANS TRY TO AVOID IT.

498
00:26:33,633 --> 00:26:36,178
HUMANS SAY THEY AVOID IT,
BUT THEIR WORDS DON'T...

499
00:26:37,595 --> 00:26:40,099
WE'RE BEING OBSERVED.

500
00:26:44,395 --> 00:26:48,023
AH, CAPTAIN, T'POL,
I WAS JUST COMING TO SEE YOU.

501
00:26:48,023 --> 00:26:49,858
THESE ARE BRAINWAVE READINGS

502
00:26:49,858 --> 00:26:51,485
OF COMMANDER TUCKER
AND ENSIGN SATO.

503
00:26:51,485 --> 00:26:53,571
WHAT IS THE SIGNIFICANCE?

504
00:26:53,571 --> 00:26:56,282
THE PATTERNS AREN'T HUMAN.

505
00:26:56,282 --> 00:26:58,158
DID YOU KNOW THEY HAD
THIS CAPABILITY?

506
00:26:58,158 --> 00:27:00,618
HE MUST HAVE USED
DENOBULAN TECHNOLOGY.

507
00:27:04,664 --> 00:27:07,376
I SEE.

508
00:27:07,376 --> 00:27:09,545
ARE YOU RESPONSIBLE FOR WHAT
HAPPENED TO MY PATIENTS?

509
00:27:09,545 --> 00:27:11,629
WE HAD NOTHING TO DO WITH IT.

510
00:27:11,629 --> 00:27:13,173
WE COME HERE ONLY TO STUDY

511
00:27:13,173 --> 00:27:15,509
HOW PHYSICAL SPECIES
REACT TO THE UNKNOWN.

512
00:27:15,509 --> 00:27:18,804
YOU CAN HELP BY TELLING US
HOW YOU DETECTED OUR PRESENCE.

513
00:27:18,804 --> 00:27:21,348
THAT HAPPENS IN LESS THAN 2%
OF OUR MISSIONS.

514
00:27:23,809 --> 00:27:25,894
COMMANDER TUCKER AND ENSIGN SATO
WERE SEDATED.

515
00:27:25,894 --> 00:27:28,564
THEY SHOULDN'T HAVE BEEN ABLE
TO STAND AND TALK.

516
00:27:28,564 --> 00:27:30,399
IT'S BEEN SO LONG
SINCE WE HAD PHYSICAL FORM,

517
00:27:30,399 --> 00:27:32,734
WE WEREN'T ABLE TO DISTINGUISH
SLEEP FROM SEDATION.

518
00:27:32,734 --> 00:27:34,153
WE'LL REMEMBER NEXT TIME.

519
00:27:35,946 --> 00:27:38,198
IS THERE ANYTHING YOU CAN DO
TO HELP MY PATIENTS?

520
00:27:38,198 --> 00:27:40,658
WE'RE HERE TO OBSERVE.
WE CAN'T INTERFERE.

521
00:27:40,658 --> 00:27:42,869
YOU'RE INTERFERING WITH ME!

522
00:27:42,869 --> 00:27:46,039
OUR SUBJECTS ARE HUMAN.
YOU'RE DENOBULAN.

523
00:27:46,039 --> 00:27:49,293
YOU WERE INHABITED A FEW HOURS
AGO -- AN INTRIGUING EXPERIENCE.

524
00:27:49,293 --> 00:27:50,877
I HAVE NO RECOLLECTION OF THAT.

525
00:27:50,877 --> 00:27:53,172
MEMORIES ARE SIMPLE TO ADJUST.

526
00:27:55,382 --> 00:27:58,385
YOU'RE GOING TO ADJUST MINE
AGAIN, HMM,

527
00:27:58,385 --> 00:28:00,929
SO I WON'T REMEMBER A WORD
OF THIS ENCOUNTER?

528
00:28:00,929 --> 00:28:03,474
OR WHAT YOU OBSERVED
IN THE DECON CHAMBER.

529
00:28:03,474 --> 00:28:06,519
IF YOU HAVE THAT ABILITY,
YOU MUST BE ABLE TO HELP
MY PATIENTS.

530
00:28:06,519 --> 00:28:07,520
WE COULD.

531
00:28:07,520 --> 00:28:09,938
BUT WE WON'T.

532
00:28:11,857 --> 00:28:15,152
THANK YOU
FOR YOUR HELP, DOCTOR.

533
00:28:15,152 --> 00:28:17,737
NO WONDER YOU ERASE MEMORIES.

534
00:28:17,737 --> 00:28:19,739
YOUR BEHAVIOR IS APPALLING!

535
00:28:21,325 --> 00:28:24,119
ACCORDING TO WHAT I READ
ON THE DOCTOR'S MEDICAL PADD,

536
00:28:24,119 --> 00:28:26,580
HE'S LEARNED HOW TO STOP
THE INFECTION.

537
00:28:26,580 --> 00:28:30,000
I'VE SEEN SEVEN OTHER SPECIES
DEVELOP THE RADIATION CURE,

538
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:31,460
BUT NEVER IN TIME.

539
00:28:31,460 --> 00:28:33,753
DID WE MAKE FIRST CONTACT
WITH ANY OF THEM?

540
00:28:33,753 --> 00:28:35,339
OF COURSE NOT.

541
00:28:35,339 --> 00:28:37,757
EXPENDING RESOURCES TO ATTEMPT
AN IMPOSSIBLE TASK

542
00:28:37,757 --> 00:28:39,635
IS NOT A SIGN OF INTELLIGENCE.

543
00:28:39,635 --> 00:28:43,472
THE CAPTAIN AND SCIENCE OFFICER
HAVE DECISIONS TO MAKE.

544
00:28:43,472 --> 00:28:46,392
WE NEED TO RETURN
TO OUR ORIGINAL HOSTS.

545
00:28:49,853 --> 00:28:52,105
FOR THE RADIATION
TO DESTROY THE VIRUS

546
00:28:52,105 --> 00:28:54,525
WITHOUT KILLING THE PATIENT,
IT MUST BE PRECISELY FOCUSED.

547
00:28:54,525 --> 00:28:56,569
THE EMITTERS IN THE DECON
CHAMBER AREN'T SUITABLE.

548
00:28:56,569 --> 00:28:59,405
BUT THE BIO-SCANNER
IN SICKBAY IS.

549
00:28:59,405 --> 00:29:02,575
TO MOVE THEM FROM DECON
TO SICKBAY,

550
00:29:02,575 --> 00:29:06,119
WE'LL NEED TO EXPAND
THE QUARANTINED AREA.

551
00:29:06,119 --> 00:29:08,080
THAT WON'T BE A PROBLEM.

552
00:29:08,080 --> 00:29:10,290
WE'RE GONNA MAKE THIS WORK.

553
00:29:15,837 --> 00:29:18,465
[ ALARM BLARES ]

554
00:29:18,465 --> 00:29:21,594
ENSIGN SATO'S CONDITION
IS DETERIORATING.

555
00:29:21,594 --> 00:29:22,886
WE NEED TO HURRY.

556
00:29:35,566 --> 00:29:37,901
ENGAGING QUARANTINE.

557
00:29:37,901 --> 00:29:41,154
REED TO BRIDGE.
I CONFIRM A POSITIVE SEAL.

558
00:29:41,154 --> 00:29:43,990
ENVIRONMENTAL SYSTEMS
ARE ISOLATED.

559
00:29:43,990 --> 00:29:47,411
<i>ENTERING THE QUARANTINE ZONE.</i>

560
00:30:08,807 --> 00:30:10,809
SHE'S GOING INTO OLIGEMIC SHOCK.

561
00:30:10,809 --> 00:30:12,436
CAPTAIN, SHE'S DYING.

562
00:30:15,855 --> 00:30:17,691
[ GASPING ]

563
00:30:24,072 --> 00:30:26,492
GET HER ON THE BIO-SCAN BED.

564
00:30:31,037 --> 00:30:32,331
SHE'S STOPPED BREATHING!

565
00:30:38,128 --> 00:30:40,964
SOMEONE ALWAYS DIES.

566
00:30:46,845 --> 00:30:48,263
[ SIGHS ] HOSHI.

567
00:30:48,263 --> 00:30:50,641
-[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]
-PHLOX!

568
00:30:53,268 --> 00:30:55,646
-AH!
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

569
00:30:55,646 --> 00:30:58,148
THIS EQUIPMENT'S NOT
DESIGNED FOR E.V. GLOVES.

570
00:30:59,733 --> 00:31:02,569
-I'LL BE YOUR HANDS.
-NO, CAPTAIN, NO!

571
00:31:02,569 --> 00:31:05,030
RIGHT NOW,
<i>ENTERPRISE</i> NEEDS A DOCTOR

572
00:31:05,030 --> 00:31:06,573
MORE THAN IT NEEDS A CAPTAIN.

573
00:31:28,011 --> 00:31:31,056
ATTACH THE LEADS
20 CENTIMETERS APART.

574
00:31:35,018 --> 00:31:37,521
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

575
00:31:37,521 --> 00:31:41,400
IN 800 YEARS, NO ONE'S
EVER DONE THAT BEFORE?

576
00:31:41,400 --> 00:31:42,693
NO.

577
00:31:42,693 --> 00:31:44,903
NOT ONCE THEY KNOW
IT'S HOPELESS.

578
00:31:44,903 --> 00:31:46,822
<i>YOU NEED TO INJECT 40 UNITS</i>

579
00:31:46,822 --> 00:31:48,907
OF TRINEPHEDRINE INTO HER HEART.

580
00:31:49,991 --> 00:31:51,326
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

581
00:31:51,326 --> 00:31:53,787
THAT CAN'T GO DEEP ENOUGH.

582
00:32:01,795 --> 00:32:03,797
OLD-FASHIONED, BUT EFFECTIVE.

583
00:32:05,507 --> 00:32:08,134
ANGLE IT SLIGHTLY MORE
TO THE RIGHT.

584
00:32:08,134 --> 00:32:12,681
NOW, IN ONE QUICK MOTION,
INSERT IT THREE CENTIMETERS.

585
00:32:14,892 --> 00:32:16,184
PRESS THE ACTIVATOR.

586
00:32:21,565 --> 00:32:23,024
CLEAR!

587
00:32:24,276 --> 00:32:27,028
[ DEFIBRILLATOR ZAPS ]

588
00:32:32,075 --> 00:32:33,368
COME ON, HOSHI.

589
00:32:35,495 --> 00:32:37,915
300 MILLIJOULES.

590
00:32:37,915 --> 00:32:40,626
[ DEFIBRILLATOR ZAPS ]

591
00:32:45,798 --> 00:32:46,882
CAPTAIN.

592
00:32:46,882 --> 00:32:48,091
AGAIN!

593
00:32:49,301 --> 00:32:51,136
340.

594
00:32:51,136 --> 00:32:53,012
[ DEFIBRILLATOR ZAPS ]

595
00:32:54,640 --> 00:32:56,767
[ FLATLINE ]

596
00:32:56,767 --> 00:32:59,269
SHE'S GONE.

597
00:33:03,565 --> 00:33:06,318
CAPTAIN, HELP ME
WITH COMMANDER TUCKER.

598
00:33:07,986 --> 00:33:09,571
HOW MANY HAVE TO DIE

599
00:33:09,571 --> 00:33:12,157
BEFORE YOU WILL ADMIT HUMANS
ARE DIFFERENT?

600
00:33:12,157 --> 00:33:14,117
WE NEED TO STOP THIS.

601
00:33:14,117 --> 00:33:16,870
I WILL NOT DEPART
FROM PROTOCOL.

602
00:33:16,870 --> 00:33:18,204
THE INCIDENT ISN'T OVER.

603
00:33:18,204 --> 00:33:20,582
WHEN THE FIRST DEATH
OCCURS ON THE SHIP,

604
00:33:20,582 --> 00:33:23,794
THERE'S A 68% CHANCE THE REST OF
THE CREW WILL BECOME INFECTED.

605
00:33:23,794 --> 00:33:25,754
AND WHAT MORE WILL THAT TEACH US
ABOUT THEM?

606
00:33:25,754 --> 00:33:29,007
ALL THIS WOULD HAVE HAPPENED
WHETHER WE WERE HERE OR NOT.

607
00:33:29,007 --> 00:33:31,176
WE ARE NOT RESPONSIBLE.

608
00:33:32,928 --> 00:33:35,013
MAYBE WE SHOULD BE.

609
00:33:41,687 --> 00:33:44,147
WE NEED TO MOVE HIM
INTO THE SCANNER.

610
00:33:44,147 --> 00:33:46,441
[ PANTING ]

611
00:33:54,157 --> 00:33:56,576
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

612
00:34:09,715 --> 00:34:11,842
[ GASPS ]

613
00:34:11,842 --> 00:34:15,261
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

614
00:34:15,261 --> 00:34:17,681
IT DIDN'T WORK.

615
00:34:17,681 --> 00:34:19,140
I'M SORRY, CAPTAIN.

616
00:34:24,354 --> 00:34:26,064
NOT YOUR FAULT, DOCTOR.

617
00:34:26,064 --> 00:34:28,358
THERE'S NOTHING MORE I CAN DO
FOR COMMANDER TUCKER,

618
00:34:28,358 --> 00:34:30,235
BUT YOU'VE STILL GOT
A FEW HOURS.

619
00:34:30,235 --> 00:34:33,822
THERE HAS TO BE SOMETHING ELSE
I -- I CAN TRY.

620
00:34:35,824 --> 00:34:39,745
YOU SHOULD CONTINUE YOUR WORK
ON THE BRIDGE --

621
00:34:39,745 --> 00:34:42,121
LESS CHANCE OF SOMETHING
GOING WRONG WITH YOUR SUIT.

622
00:34:42,121 --> 00:34:44,917
I WON'T GIVE UP.

623
00:34:44,917 --> 00:34:47,335
YOU KNOW WHERE TO FIND ME.

624
00:35:08,982 --> 00:35:10,817
ARCHER TO T'POL.

625
00:35:10,817 --> 00:35:14,279
T'POL HERE, CAPTAIN.

626
00:35:14,279 --> 00:35:17,198
<i>I TAKE IT</i>
<i>YOU'VE BEEN WATCHING.</i>

627
00:35:17,198 --> 00:35:18,992
I HAVE.

628
00:35:18,992 --> 00:35:21,870
<i>THEN YOU KNOW</i>
<i>YOU'RE IN COMMAND.</i>

629
00:35:21,870 --> 00:35:24,748
YES, CAPTAIN.

630
00:35:24,748 --> 00:35:28,752
<i>I WOULD LIKE TO THINK</i>
<i>YOU'LL STAY IN COMMAND.</i>

631
00:35:28,752 --> 00:35:33,966
<i>DON'T LET ADMIRAL GARDNER SNEAK</i>
<i>IN SOMEONE OVER YOUR HEAD.</i>

632
00:35:33,966 --> 00:35:36,175
I'LL DO MY BEST.

633
00:35:36,175 --> 00:35:38,177
<i>I KNOW YOU WILL.</i>

634
00:35:46,019 --> 00:35:49,106
<i>I NEED TO LOOK AFTER</i>
<i>TRIP NOW.</i>

635
00:35:51,066 --> 00:35:53,234
WE'LL TALK AGAIN WHEN...

636
00:35:55,988 --> 00:35:58,156
WE'LL TALK AGAIN.

637
00:35:58,156 --> 00:36:00,158
CAPTAIN.

638
00:36:00,158 --> 00:36:04,162
IF COMMANDER TUCKER
BECOMES CONSCIOUS...

639
00:36:04,162 --> 00:36:06,748
<i>I'LL LET YOU KNOW RIGHT AWAY.</i>

640
00:36:10,209 --> 00:36:11,878
<i>ARCHER OUT.</i>

641
00:36:17,175 --> 00:36:19,678
[ WHEEZING ]

642
00:36:58,091 --> 00:37:01,678
I HAVE SUCH RESPECT FOR YOU,
CAPTAIN ARCHER.

643
00:37:06,892 --> 00:37:08,101
TRIP?

644
00:37:08,101 --> 00:37:09,686
NOT EXACTLY.

645
00:37:10,979 --> 00:37:13,523
I'M AN ORGANIAN,

646
00:37:13,523 --> 00:37:16,317
A NON-PHYSICAL LIFE-FORM.

647
00:37:16,317 --> 00:37:18,611
TRIP IS MY HOST.

648
00:37:20,655 --> 00:37:22,824
WHAT DID YOU DO TO HIM?

649
00:37:22,824 --> 00:37:24,576
NOTHING.

650
00:37:24,576 --> 00:37:26,244
WE NEVER INTERFERE

651
00:37:26,244 --> 00:37:29,247
IN THE NATURAL DEVELOPMENT
OF OTHER SPECIES.

652
00:37:29,247 --> 00:37:30,582
WE ONLY OBSERVE.

653
00:37:30,582 --> 00:37:34,502
DID YOU KNOW
ABOUT THE SILICON VIRUS?

654
00:37:34,502 --> 00:37:37,589
THAT'S WHY WE COME HERE --

655
00:37:37,589 --> 00:37:42,969
TO SEE HOW DIFFERENT SPECIES
REACT WHEN THEY ENCOUNTER IT.

656
00:37:42,969 --> 00:37:46,723
YOU KNEW ABOUT THE VIRUS THAT
KILLED TWO MEMBERS OF MY CREW,

657
00:37:46,723 --> 00:37:48,641
AND YOU DIDN'T WARN US?

658
00:37:48,641 --> 00:37:52,771
I WANTED TO,
BUT IT'S NOT UP TO ME.

659
00:37:52,771 --> 00:37:55,440
YOU'RE BREAKING
EVERY RULE WE HAVE.

660
00:37:55,440 --> 00:37:57,400
BECAUSE THEY DON'T APPLY
TO THIS SPECIES.

661
00:37:57,400 --> 00:37:59,736
THAT IS NOT OUR DECISION
TO MAKE.

662
00:37:59,736 --> 00:38:01,654
IF WE DON'T CHALLENGE
THE RULES --

663
00:38:01,654 --> 00:38:03,322
I DON'T CARE ABOUT YOUR RULES.

664
00:38:03,322 --> 00:38:05,366
TELL ME WHAT HAPPENS
TO TRIP AND HOSHI

665
00:38:05,366 --> 00:38:07,368
WHEN YOU'RE FINISHED
WITH THEIR BODIES.

666
00:38:07,368 --> 00:38:10,247
WE HAVE TO LEAVE THEM
AS THEY ARE.

667
00:38:12,582 --> 00:38:14,417
DEAD?

668
00:38:20,381 --> 00:38:23,635
I UNDERSTAND
WHY YOU WON'T GET INVOLVED

669
00:38:23,635 --> 00:38:26,387
WITH A SPECIES'
NATURAL DEVELOPMENT.

670
00:38:26,387 --> 00:38:30,809
I'VE FACED THAT DECISION MYSELF.
IT ISN'T AN EASY ONE TO MAKE.

671
00:38:30,809 --> 00:38:32,351
THEN WE AGREE.

672
00:38:32,351 --> 00:38:33,812
NO, WE DON'T.

673
00:38:33,812 --> 00:38:36,439
OUR ENCOUNTER WITH THE VIRUS
WAS AN ACCIDENT,

674
00:38:36,439 --> 00:38:38,566
ONE THAT YOU
COULD HAVE PREVENTED.

675
00:38:38,566 --> 00:38:41,486
THEN HOW WOULD WE
EVER LEARN ABOUT YOU?

676
00:38:41,486 --> 00:38:44,739
ASK US. TALK TO US.

677
00:38:45,991 --> 00:38:47,909
JUST LIKE YOU'RE DOING NOW.

678
00:38:47,909 --> 00:38:50,287
TALKING IS A LIMITED FORM
OF COMMUNICATION FOR US.

679
00:38:50,287 --> 00:38:53,039
WE'RE MUCH MORE ADVANCED
THAN HUMANS.

680
00:38:53,039 --> 00:38:56,084
NOT FROM WHERE I'M STANDING.

681
00:38:57,669 --> 00:39:01,673
MAYBE YOU'VE EVOLVED INTO BEINGS

682
00:39:01,673 --> 00:39:03,758
WITH ABILITIES
I CAN'T COMPREHEND,

683
00:39:03,758 --> 00:39:05,593
BUT YOU'VE PAID
A HELL OF A PRICE.

684
00:39:05,593 --> 00:39:10,932
YOU'VE LOST COMPASSION
AND EMPATHY --

685
00:39:10,932 --> 00:39:13,226
THINGS THAT GIVE LIFE MEANING.

686
00:39:13,226 --> 00:39:17,605
AND IF THAT'S WHAT IT TAKES
TO BE ADVANCED...

687
00:39:20,650 --> 00:39:22,861
I DON'T WANT ANY PART OF IT.

688
00:39:22,861 --> 00:39:26,990
WE'RE LEAVING NOW, CAPTAIN.

689
00:39:26,990 --> 00:39:29,617
YOU WON'T REMEMBER A THING
ABOUT OUR PRESENCE.

690
00:39:29,617 --> 00:39:31,286
[ COUGHING ]

691
00:39:31,286 --> 00:39:33,621
AND IN THREE HOURS,
YOU'LL DIE AS WELL.

692
00:39:34,622 --> 00:39:36,624
NO.

693
00:39:36,624 --> 00:39:39,585
WE HAVE THE POWER
TO SAVE THEM ALL.

694
00:39:39,585 --> 00:39:40,962
ARE YOU DEFYING ME?

695
00:39:40,962 --> 00:39:44,174
I'M DEFYING THE ENTIRE PROTOCOL.

696
00:39:44,174 --> 00:39:46,801
WHAT ARCHER HAS DONE TODAY,

697
00:39:46,801 --> 00:39:50,138
HIS ACT OF COMPASSION --

698
00:39:50,138 --> 00:39:52,557
YOU'VE NEVER
WITNESSED THAT BEFORE.

699
00:39:52,557 --> 00:39:54,684
IN TIME,
WE'LL STUDY OTHER HUMANS.

700
00:39:54,684 --> 00:39:57,312
THERE'S ANOTHER WAY.

701
00:39:57,312 --> 00:40:01,316
EXPERIENCE COMPASSION
FOR YOURSELF.

702
00:40:03,318 --> 00:40:08,114
YOU WANT TO KNOW WHAT IT MEANS
TO BE HUMAN,

703
00:40:08,114 --> 00:40:10,075
YOU NEED TO DO MORE
THAN OBSERVE.

704
00:40:16,664 --> 00:40:19,376
-[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]
-Archer to the bridge.

705
00:40:19,376 --> 00:40:20,793
T'POL. GO AHEAD.

706
00:40:20,793 --> 00:40:22,712
You wanted to know
when Trip was awake.

707
00:40:22,712 --> 00:40:24,047
YES.

708
00:40:24,047 --> 00:40:25,924
Well, you better
get down here,

709
00:40:25,924 --> 00:40:28,009
because he's talking up a storm,
and so is Hoshi.

710
00:40:28,009 --> 00:40:30,136
-CAPTAIN, HOSHI --
-You too, Phlox.

711
00:40:30,136 --> 00:40:33,056
Maybe one of you can tell me
what the hell just happened.

712
00:40:36,184 --> 00:40:37,560
[ CHUCKLES ]

713
00:40:37,560 --> 00:40:40,479
YOU'RE ALL
COMPLETELY FREE OF THE VIRUS.

714
00:40:40,479 --> 00:40:42,357
IT HAS TO HAVE BEEN
A DELAYED REACTION

715
00:40:42,357 --> 00:40:44,901
TO COMMANDER TUCKER'S
RADIATION TREATMENT.

716
00:40:44,901 --> 00:40:46,903
BUT HOW IT SPILLED OVER
TO YOU AND HOSHI,

717
00:40:46,903 --> 00:40:49,822
I HAVE NO EXPLANATION.

718
00:40:49,822 --> 00:40:51,950
OBVIOUSLY,
THE PATHOGEN'S BEHAVIOR

719
00:40:51,950 --> 00:40:53,952
IS MORE UNPREDICTABLE
THAN WE ASSUMED.

720
00:40:53,952 --> 00:40:56,537
I'M SURE SOMEONE AT STARFLEET
MEDICAL WILL FIGURE IT OUT.

721
00:40:56,537 --> 00:41:00,792
BUT FOR NOW, WE'RE GONNA LEAVE
A WARNING BEACON IN ORBIT HERE

722
00:41:00,792 --> 00:41:03,836
AND MAKE SURE
WHAT HAPPENED TO US

723
00:41:03,836 --> 00:41:06,798
NEVER HAPPENS
TO ANYONE AGAIN.

724
00:41:06,798 --> 00:41:09,759
YOU REALIZE THE CONSEQUENCES
OF WHAT WE'VE DONE.

725
00:41:09,759 --> 00:41:12,053
WE WILL NEVER BE ABLE TO OBSERVE
ANOTHER SPECIES

726
00:41:12,053 --> 00:41:13,638
ENCOUNTER THIS VIRUS.

727
00:41:13,638 --> 00:41:16,015
GOOD.

728
00:41:16,015 --> 00:41:18,935
I'M LOOKING FORWARD
TO MAKING MY FIRST REPORT.

729
00:41:18,935 --> 00:41:22,355
AFTER 10,000 YEARS,
THE RULES NEED TO CHANGE.

730
00:41:24,023 --> 00:41:26,776
THESE HUMANS HAVE NOT BEEN
A GOOD INFLUENCE ON YOU.

731
00:41:26,776 --> 00:41:29,028
I WOULD NOT ENCOURAGE
FURTHER ENCOUNTERS.

732
00:41:29,028 --> 00:41:30,822
I DON'T THINK
WE CAN AVOID THEM.

733
00:41:30,822 --> 00:41:33,032
I'M GOING TO RECOMMEND
THAT WE START PREPARATION

734
00:41:33,032 --> 00:41:35,410
FOR AN OFFICIAL
FIRST-CONTACT MISSION.

735
00:41:35,410 --> 00:41:36,744
INDEED.

736
00:41:36,744 --> 00:41:38,621
AND AT THE RATE
THEY'RE PROGRESSING,

737
00:41:38,621 --> 00:41:40,206
THAT'LL BARELY GIVE US
5,000 YEARS TO PREPARE.

738
00:41:40,206 --> 00:41:42,250
THEN WE'D BETTER GET STARTED.
